review.title: One of my favorite Cereals and Snacks!
review.review: One of my favorite cereals.I remember eating this most of my life. Each frosted mini-wheat biscuit one side with frosting and the other side with whole grain wheat. It's healthy and a great way to keep your energy up. To me it's not just for breakfast, I take snack bag and I eat them as a snack when I'm on the road. Heck I eat them for dinner lol It was my first time using Amazon Prime Pantry, which I have to say they are Great! Awesome choices, Fast with shipment and everything they sent is fresh any well packed. I'm a very happy person.

review.title: Frosted Mini Wheats
review.review: Great tasting cereal for breakfast, or for a late night snack. Not too sweet, but still sweet enough. I love eating cereal at night more than I do in the morning. I found Amazon had this at a great price so I happily added a box into my prime pantry box, it arrived in great condition!

review.title: Chocolatey & Gluten Free!!!
review.review: This gluten free cereal has a delightful chocolatey taste. I love that it's GF, since I try to stick with GF as much as possible.

review.title: Great Price, made even better!
review.review: Between my children and myself we eat a box of little bites every couple days. I love the flavor and texture of this cereal and it is pretty healthy too. For my kids this cereal is a treat, (I don't allow junk cereal in the house). At the local grocery store it is over $3.50 a box. I enrolled in auto ship and it is closer to $2 a box. Be prepared though, there is a little more breakage to the product than when I buy at the grocery store but for the price I don't mind, that is the reason for the four star rating.

review.title: Another winner!
review.review: Local stores dont have this flavor. I was curious since I like the peanut butter and chocolate flavors. This cinnamon flavor is my favorite! I like that these are not super sweet and no fake tasting flavors. I quickly ordered more boxes!

review.title: It's ok
review.review: This cereal is ok. I mean, my kids will eat it. And since my kids are super picky and can't have gluten or milk, that's saying something. However, this has no nutritional value whatsoever. If it wasn't for the milk, my kids might as well just eat a bowl of sugar.

review.title: ANOTHER FAVORITE FAVORITE
review.review: This is one of my granddaughter's favorite cereals. I like to buy items that I know will be appreciated. This was a good price for the size (two 23.6 ounce boxes). When I bought it on subscription last month the cost of $10.19 plus tax was a good buy. An added benefit is that General Mills cereals have 'Boxtops for Education' to cut off the boxes to send in to school. Granddaughter and her class get recognized and the PTA gets to buy things for school.

When I was pregnant I used to have my mother in law ship 6 boxes at a time of this over from South Carolina since they don’t sell it in jersey. I honestly thought there’s no way amazon will have it, I’m glad I was wrong. It is like marshmallow krispie crack, it’s addicting. I promised my self not to buy another box, because once there in my house, I can’t stop eating them.

list.name: Cap'n Crunch Crunch Berries
list.description: Captain Crunch's Crunch Berries combines crunchy sweetened corn and oat biscuits with delicious fruit flavored berry shapes

review.title: Good Ole' Captain Crunch!
review.review: You just can't go wrong with Captain Crunch Cereal. I used to eat this all the time growing up and the cereal is completely addictive. If I want a snack later after dinner, I grab a bowl of cereal. It is quick and easy and so delicious! It still has the classic original squares and the colored berries which are my favorite part of the cereal! Add some milk and you are all ready to go. It doesn't leave a bad or after taste in your mouth like some cereals. It never stays in my milk long enough to get soggy, so it is always crunchy! I love this cereal and the size you get for the value is great!

review.title: Delicious
review.review: What's to say besides the fact that this is the greatest cereal ever? Nothing.

review.title: starsAmiibo is ALL that matters here!

review.title: Outrageous price for a tiny box.
review.review: I bought this for my son who is Mario obsessed, and paid a stupid amount for cereal. I even made fun of myself for paying $13 for a tony box of cereal, but I didn't think I could get it anywhere else and I sort of assumed it was limited edition or whatever. Low and behold I go to my Fred Meyer/Kroger a few days later and it $2.99. So, as if you can't already tell - this is a complete rip off.
